.TH FM 1 "July 2026" "fm 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
fm \- Linux dual-panel file manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fm
[\fIpath1\fR] [\fIpath2\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fm
is a lightweight dual-panel file manager built with Qt6 Widgets.
It supports multi-tab browsing, file operations, favorites management,
session restore, and removable device management via UDisks2.

If an instance is already running, a new invocation sends its path
arguments to the existing window and exits (single-instance mode).

By default, the left pane opens
.I path1
and the right pane opens
.IR path2 .
If only one path is given, it opens in the left pane; the right pane
defaults to the user's home directory. With no arguments, both panes
open the home directory.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help text and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
\fIpath1\fR [\fIpath2\fR]
Optional directory paths to open in the first (and optionally second) pane.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
Dual-pane layout
Switchable horizontal/vertical orientation with adjustable split ratio.
Either pane can be hidden to use the full window width.
.TP
Multi-tab
Each pane supports multiple tabs with independent navigation history.
Tabs can be reordered by drag, cloned, or closed individually.
.TP
File operations
Copy, move, rename, delete, move to trash, and view properties.
Operations run asynchronously with a progress dialog.
Conflict resolution offers overwrite, skip, rename, or apply-to-all.
.TP
Favorites
Save the current layout and tab paths as a favorite for one-click restore.
Loading a favorite clears all existing tabs first.
.TP
Session restore
Window state, pane layout, tab paths, and sort settings are saved on exit
and restored on the next launch.
.TP
Volume management
The File menu lists mounted volumes (via QStorageInfo) and external removable
devices (via UDisks2, including unmounted ones).
Right-click a device to mount, unmount, or eject.
.TP
Configurable shortcuts
All keyboard shortcuts are customizable via the Settings dialog and take
effect immediately.

.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
Ctrl+X / Ctrl+C / Ctrl+V
Cut / Copy / Paste
.TP
F5 / F6
Copy to opposite pane / Cut to opposite pane
.TP
Ctrl+N / F7
New file / New folder
.TP
Ctrl+Shift+O
Open with...
.TP
Return / F2
Open / Rename
.TP
Delete / Shift+Delete
Move to trash / Delete permanently
.TP
Alt+Left / Alt+Right / Alt+Up
Back / Forward / Up one level
.TP
Ctrl+R
Refresh
.TP
Ctrl+T / Ctrl+W / Ctrl+Shift+T
New tab / Close tab / Clone tab
.TP
Ctrl+Tab
Switch to next tab in active pane
.TP
Tab
Switch active pane
.TP
Ctrl+H
Toggle hidden files
.TP
Alt+Return
File properties

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/fm/fm.conf
Main configuration file (INI format). Contains UI settings, column widths,
tab paths, shortcuts, favorites, and open-with associations.
Generated automatically on first run; can be safely deleted to reset to defaults.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Determines the configuration directory. Defaults to
.I ~/.config
if unset.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Determines the application data search path (for .desktop files and
mimeapps.list). Defaults to
.I ~/.local/share
if unset.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xdg-open (1),
.BR udisksctl (1),
.BR udisksd (8)
